{"word":"ὑπεραλγέω","slug":"ὑπεραλγέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὑπεραλγέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ήσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to feel pain for</i> or <i>because of</i>, <el>τινός</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to grieve exceedingly</i>, <el>τινί</el> <i>at</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b>:—<a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}